<HEADLINE>
SCURRY BARES HER CUP HOPES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By JIM THOMAS  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. _ U.S. goalkeeper Briana Scurry is on her
way to leading the team to another international championship. But
don't expect an encore to her performance ``after'' winning the
gold medal in the 1996 Olympic Games in Georgia.
</P>
<P>
   Keeping a promise she made while only half-awake, Scurry ran
naked through the streets of Athens, Ga., where the gold-medal game
was played.
</P>
<P>
   ``That was a lot of long hours and not a whole lot of sleep,''
Scurry explained this week. ````Sports Illustrated'' called me at 8
a.m. and asked me what I would do if we won. I'm a woman of my
word, and I did it.''
</P>
<P>
   Scurry is making no such promises now that the U.S. team has its
first World Cup victory and is favored to win it all.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have no predictions for this World Cup,'' she said. ``I just
want to win and keep my clothes on.''
</P>
<P>
   Scurry recorded a well-deserved shutout in Saturday's opener
against Denmark, a match the U.S. team won, 3-0, at Giants Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   ``Briana made some big saves,'' forward Mia Hamm said. ``She
dominated her box, and the defense has to be happy with the
shutout.'' &QL; 
Stage fright &QL; 
Women's soccer has yet to catch on in Denmark, where handball is
the most popular sport among females. The soccer national team had
hoped that a good showing in the World Cup would help change that,
but the Danes drew the unfortunate assignment of playing the United
States in the opener.
</P>
<P>
   Denmark Coach Jorgen Hvidemose said the players had been nervous
before the match but settled down once they took the field.
</P>
<P>
   ``Playing the United States was a very special match for us,''
he said.
</P>
<P>
   The sellout crowd of 78,972 had to be intimidating to the Danes.
They had never before played in front of a crowd larger than
20,000.
</P>
<P>
   Or consider it from this perspective: There are an estimated 7.5
million females playing soccer in the United States. The entire
population of Denmark is 5 million. &QL; 
Thoughts of home &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Mexican national team dedicated its World Cup opener
Saturday against Brazil at Giants Stadium to the victims of the
earthquake Tuesday in central Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   The 6.7-magnitude quake left at least 19 dead, dozens injured
and destroyed numerous buildings.
</P>
<P>
   ``We all feel very sad about what happened,'' Mexico Coach
Leonardo Cuellar said.
</P>
<P>
   The Mexicans were clearly overmatched against Brazil _ perhaps
the top team in Group B _ losing, 7-1. &QL; 
Corner kicks &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Canadian Sonia Denoncourt was the referee in the United
State-Denmark match, her second straight World Cup opener. All the
referees in this Cup are women, a first for the event.
</P>
<P>
   The most famous Brazilian, and the best-known of all soccer
players, was in attendance at Giants Stadium. Pele was spotted
cheering on Brazil in its match against Mexico. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
