   ECOMMERCE-WEDDINGS (Undated) _ The early contenders to dominate
the national bridal market do not come from the ranks of the
industry's traditional players _ in this case, the bridal magazines
and large department store chains _ but rather from the world of
well-financed Internet start-ups founded by people in their 20s
with personal experience in the ways of modern wedding planning.
And what is even more surprising is how widely divergent these
new-wave business models are. By Evan I. Schwartz.
</P>
