Parc research lab have published an academic study of Web traffic
patterns that appears to underscore the value of so-called portals
as a business strategy. By John Markoff.
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-POLL (Undated) _ In the latest sign of growing confidence
about the Year 2000 computer challenge, a poll last week of
managers involved in corporate Year 2000 projects found that 83
percent expect expect Year 2000 glitches to have little or no
impact on their business. By Barnaby J, Feder.
</P>
<P>
   TELECOM-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ The steps that
telecommunications, cable and networking companies need to take now
to prosper in the Internet age do not mesh with the short-term
expectations of Wall Street _ a quandary apparent in the recent
takeover battle for U S West, the smallest of the Baby Bells, and
Frontier Communications International, one of the nation's largest
long-distance phone companies. By Laura M. Holson.
</P>
