<DOCNO> NYT19990620.0061 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-20 16:15 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2705 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     06-20 0733
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HOW DOES THE CALIFORNIA GARDEN GROW? &LR;
</P>
<P>
   If politics were a garden, posited state Attorney General
 &UR; Bill Lockyer &LR; , commencement speaker at McGeorge School of Law in
Sacramento (as reported by the Los Angeles Times):
</P>
<P>
   `` &UR; Jerry Brown &LR;  would be bamboo. The introduction seemed like a
good idea at the time, but you can't get rid of the stuff.''
</P>
<P>
   `` &UR; Bob Dornan  &LR; would be an avocado, green on the outside,
essentially a nut within.''
</P>
<P>
   `` &UR; Willie Brown &LR;  would be sweet corn, (which) provides an earful
and carries a lot of greenery, sucks up all nutrients in the
vicinity.''
</P>
<P>
   `` &UR; Pete Wilson &LR;  would be iceberg lettuce; big head, difficult to
transport back East.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHITE HOUSE MAKES NEW YEARS PLANS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The Clinton administration was waiting until July 4 to announce
plans of a mega-centennial celebration in Washington, but the Wall
Street Journal jumped the gun last week, reporting that the
Clintons are planning a $10 million gala on the Washington Mall.
</P>
<P>
   This celebration, to be paid for by private donations, will
include live music produced by  &UR; Quincy Jones &LR;  and a 17-minute film
created by  &UR; Steven Spielberg &LR;  and narrated by big Bill himself.
Music for the film will be composed by  &UR; John Williams &LR; , who writes
music for most Spielberg movies.
</P>
<P>
   Fund-raiser  &UR; Terence McAuliffe &LR;  says that big corporations who
donate money will be recognized and identified. ``I don't see this
thing competing at all with other Democratic causes,'' he said.
``Clearly this is not about politics.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   - A bogus eBay auction for 200 pounds of cocaine was pulled off
the site after being posted for 18 hours, reports MSNBC.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; - Mark Hetts &LR; , author of a syndicated home repair column for
Universal Press Syndicate, is the sort of professional to have
noticed that the ``small rubber debris filter in the base of
urinals in men's rooms at Universal Studio's City Walk mall (in Los
Angeles) are imprinted with the words, `Just Say No to Drugs.'''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; - Camryn Manheim &LR;  will be Lane Bryant's first celebrity
spokesperson this fall, reports Advertising Age.
</P>
<P>
   - The Milanese newspaper Corriere Della Sera has clarified its
report that  &UR; Daniel Day-Lewis  &LR; was apprenticed to a shoemaker,
saying that in fact, he was ordering several pairs of custom-made
shoes, had several fittings, and found the process so interesting
that he returned on his own several times to watch them being made.
</P>
<P>
   - This weekend's royal wedding reminded  &UR; Al Guthertz &LR;  of
standing in front of Buckingham Palace waving to royal newlyweds
 &UR; Andrew  &LR; and  &UR; Sarah &LR; , when he realized that kids next to him ``were
looking into my face instead of up at the balcony,'' and his pocket
was picked. In related travel news,  &UR; Agnes Chen Brown &LR;  writes from
St. Petersburg that she was standing in a crowd, worried about her
possessions, looking at a boy of 12 or so who said to her in
perfect English, ``I'm not going to steal your bag.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; GUYS WITHOUT CLOTHES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   - A new but instantly famous series of TV ads for Beyond.com
features an actor the ad calls  &UR; Reed Woodson &LR; , working at home
totally naked, thanks to his great software (and thanks to TV
digitalization in the crotch area). The ad was created by San
Francisco agency Leagas Delaney, and the name ``Reed Woodson'' is
that of a 26-year-old ad man.
</P>
<P>
   Woodson knew the theme of the spot, he told Personals, ``but
didn't know that my name was going to go in there until I saw it on
TV. It was a nice surprise, in a way. In this business, everyone
likes notoriety. This is one way to get it.''
</P>
<P>
   Woodson's mother thinks ``It's one of my greatest business
accomplishments to date.''
</P>
<P>
   - Nude Recreation Week, July 5 through 11, will be celebrated
with Dress Poker games at the Olive Dell Ranch in Colton, Calif
CA &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   &UR; - Frank Moonan  &LR; is relieved at the Journal of Urology's report
that the old saw about men becoming temporary impotent as a result
of wearing briefs isn't true. Temperatures inside both styles of
underwear are barely different, and the sperm swims (breaststroke)
with the same fervor regardless.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``No! Not at all! Tommy has been neutered or spayed. What do you
call it?''
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; Pamela Anderson Lee &LR;  to TV Guide, denying rumors that she's
pregnant.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
