<P>
   (Coded e)
</P>
<P>
   TV-SOAPS-DECLINE (New York) _ Buffeted by the entry of women
into the workplace, the changing routines for the ones at home and
competition from real-life soap operas ranging from Jerry Springer
to l'Affaire Lewinsky, soap opera audiences are plummeting. The
changes, which have been creeping up for more than a decade, are
sending the industry into a sense of gloom and providing an
illustrative commentary on some of the changes in American life and
entertainment. By Peter Applebome.
</P>
