<HEADER>
A2850 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GEN-CYBER-LADN     06-20 0330
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GEN-CYBER-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ODDS OF RODMAN COMEBACK WORRY US MORE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ An on-line sports betting site called
Intertops.com (www.intertops.com), a fully licensed company in St.
John's, Antigua, has laid claim to establishing the first odds _
5-to-6 _ on Michael Jordan's return to the NBA to play now that
Phil Jackson has taken over the Lakers.
</P>
<P>
   Internet gamblers can also bet against the likelihood that
Jordan will come out of retirement _ currently posted at even
money.
</P>
<P>
   Phil's other cause: Democratic presidential candidate Bill
Bradley has a campaign website (billbradley.com) that will send
e-mails about his appearances, such as the one he had this past
week in L.A.
</P>
<P>
   Not even game-used: It was item number 115415780 on the ebay.com
online auction site _ a USC football helmet that used to belong to
quarterback Jason Thomas, who has since transferred. First bid was
$100.00. The high bid was $162.50.
</P>
<P>
   NBA playground: Among the toys to play with during the NBA
Finals on the league's official Website (http://nba.com) is a
section on the odd records that have been set during the NBA
Finals. Did you know that on the day Magic Johnson set the rookie
record for points (42) to lead the Lakers to the title in Game 6
against Philadelphia in 1980, he also set an NBA Finals record with
10 turnovers? Those are just two of Johnson's 19 NBA Finals
records, more than anyone in history.
</P>
<P>
   The site also has a Quicktime video clip of Jerry West making
his 60-footer during the 1970 NBA Finals
(nba.com/theater/video/1970ot.avi).
</P>
<P>
   Net volleys: For the fifth straight year, Wimbledon's official
site (www.wimbledon.org) should be the best place to go for updated
info on the tournament, which takes place in the early mornings for
the next two weeks. A ``Slam Cam'' and a ``Net Cam'' allow users to
direct a robotic camera at Centre Court.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
